Sentencas: We analyze the influence of structural transformations in the nickel phase during the processes of onetime reduction and redox cycling at a temperature of 600A degrees C on the formation of strength and electric conductivity of YSZ-NiO ceramics for the anodes-substrates of solid-oxide fuel cells obtained by using the technology of cladding of YSZ powders with nickel oxide.
Titulo: Optimization of the Physicomechanical Properties of the Material of Anodes of Fuel Cells

Sentencas: After the redox treatment, we get structures guaranteeing the improved physical and mechanical characteristics of the material.
Titulo: Optimization of the Physicomechanical Properties of the Material of Anodes of Fuel Cells
